      <text>7.4.3.2 Inverse of 3 x 3 matrix â”€ Gauss elimination method</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="html">
      <text><![CDATA[<p class="HELM_exercise">Exercise</p>
<p></p><p>Use the Gauss elimination method to find the inverse of the
following matrices</p><p>\[A = {@A@},\] \[B = {@B@}.\]</p>
<ol class="HELM_parts">
<li><div>\(A^{-1}=\) [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]</div></li>
<li><div>\(B^{-1}=\) [[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans2]] [[feedback:prt2]]</div></li>
</ol>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="html">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>We can find the inverse of matrix \(A\) using the Gaussian elimination method.</p>
<p>We do this by reducing the matrix \(A\) to the identity matrix \(I\). There is no unique procedure for
    this but here is one example.</p>
<p>We first place \(A\) and \(I\) adjacent to each other.</p>
<p>{@A@} {@I@}.</p>
<p>We now proceed by changing the columns of \(A\) left to right to reduce \(A\) to the form {@upper@}, where \(n\) can be any number. This form is called upper triangular.</p>
<p>First we swap row 1 and row 2.</p>
<p>\[{@A@} {@I@} R1 \leftrightarrow R2 \longrightarrow {@matrixa@} {@I2@} \].</p>
<p>Now we subtract {@a[2,1]@} times row 1 from row 2 and {@a[3,1]@} times row 1 from row 3.</p>
<p>\[{@matrixa@} {@I2@} R2 - {@a[2,1]@} R1, R3 - {@a[3,1]@} R1 \longrightarrow {@matrixb@} {@I3@}\]</p>
<p>Then we divide row 2 by {@b[2,2]@} and subtract {@b[3,2]@} times row 2 from row 3.</p>
<p>\[{@matrixb@} {@I3@} R2/{@b[2,2]@}, R3 - {@b[3,2]@} R2 \longrightarrow {@matrixc@} {@I4@}\].</p>
<p>Finally we divide row 3 by {@c[3,3]@}.</p>
\[{@matrixc@} {@I4@} R3/{@c[3,3]@} \longrightarrow {@matrixd@}
{@I5@}\]
<p>We would usually proceed by changing the columns of \(A\) right to left to reduce \(A\) to the form {@I@}. However, for this question we already obtained zeros above the main diagonal after we swapped row 1 and row 2.</p>
<p>So we have,</p>
<p>\[A^{-1} = {@I5@}.\]</p>
<p>The method can be used to determine \(B^{-1}\) similarly.</p>]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
